10 AS INTRODUCED
11 An Act relating to easements; enacting the Oklahoma
Uniform Easement Relocation Act of 2025; defining
12 terms; provides applicability of act to certain
easements; excludes certain easements from relation;
13 establishes the right of a property owner to relocate
an easement in certain circumstances; provides that a
14 property owner may commence a civil action to
relocate an easement; provides the requirements for
15 commencing a civil action to relocate an easement;
provides the court guidelines in creating an order
16 for relocation of an easement; requiring the
recordation of certain documents prior to relocation
17 of an easement; providing for reasonable expenses
related to the relocation of an easement; requires
18 the parties to a civil action for easement relocation
to act in good faith in facilitating relocation;
19 provides when a proposed easement relocation is
considered to be final and complete; provides and
20 limits the effect of an easement relocation; provides
that the right of a property to relocate an easement
21 under this act cannot be waived, excluded, or
restricted by agreement; provides that the law should
22 be applied and construed to promote uniformity with
other states that enact the act; provides relation to
23 the Electronic Signatures in Global and National
Commerce Act; provides that the act applies to an
24 easement created before, on, or after the effective
